About Event

​ **🎬 Date & Time:**

April 12, 3:00 PM – 10:00 PM

• **Film Screening:** The New Parkway Theater (3:00–5:00 PM)

• **VIP Reception:** Nearby private residence (5:30–10:00 PM)

* * *

​Join us for a special screening of **_[The Great Yawn of History](https://www.imdb.com/title/tt31016912/)_** by **[Aliyar Rasti](https://www.imdb.com/name/nm9932495/?ref_=tt_ov_dr_1)** which received the Special Jury Prize in the Encounters section of Berlinale 2024, featuring **Saber Abar** and **[Mohammad Aghebati](https://www.imdb.com/name/nm5396916/?ref_=tt_ov_st_2)**.

​ [Film Teaser: Youtube](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cY0RMJNst-8&ab_channel=Berlinale-BerlinInternationalFilmFestival)

​If you are interested in the independent cinema scene of Iran and its emerging artists, join the **VIP Reception** afterward to meet with **[Mohammad Aghebati](https://www.imdb.com/name/nm5396916/?ref_=tt_ov_st_2)** (actor and producer) and **[Mehrnoush Alia](https://www.imdb.com/name/nm3234299/)**(producer). We will have a Q&A with them and the director. They will share stories from the hidden world of independent filmmaking in Iran and showcase emerging film projects. We’ll screen a few trailers and short films and provide drinks and food (as always).

​This is a great chance to meet fellow filmmakers, actors, and movie lovers while supporting bold, independent Iranian cinema. The collected funds will go directly to support these independent artists' upcoming film projects.

* * *

​ **Film Synopsis:** **[The Great Yawn of History](https://www.imdb.com/title/tt31016912/)**

​Beitollah dreams of gold coins in a cave. Seeking a non-religious assistant, he recruits Shoja via fake bills. They search caves across Iran unsuccessfully. An innkeeper suspects their quest and secretly follows on his motorcycle.

​ **Director Biography:** **[Aliyar Rasti](https://www.imdb.com/name/nm9932495/?ref_=tt_ov_dr_1)**

​Born in Tehran, Iran in 1988, he began his career in photography, video and video installations before gradually moving towards his true passion of filmmaking. He has made more than ten music videos for independent Iranian bands which have screened at various festivals. His first short film, _In Between_, won the Best Debut Film award at the 2018 Tirana International Film Festival. It was followed by _America_, his second short. Rasti's debut feature film, The Great Yawn of History, received the Special Jury Prize in the Encounters section of Berlinale 2024, marking a significant milestone in his career.

​ [Film Teaser: Youtube](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cY0RMJNst-8&ab_channel=Berlinale-BerlinInternationalFilmFestival)

* * *

About Event

​ **Decode Your AMH for a Healthier Future**

​Did you know that your hormones play a crucial role in both fertility and longevity? Join us for a **FREE AMH (Anti-Müllerian Hormone) blood test** led by Dr. Kay Waud from [HRC Fertility](https://www.havingbabies.com/locations/san-francisco/). This simple yet powerful test helps assess your hormones, giving you valuable insights into your reproductive health and how it connects to your overall well-being and aging process.

📍 **Who Should Attend?**

This event is perfect for individuals aged **21-44** who want to better understand their fertility potential and how hormones impact overall health and longevity.

About Event

​\*\*Event is Full - Currently Accepting Waitlist Registrations\*\*

🔗 Event program: https://www.carbonnewbie.com/#program

​A casual conference for carbon newbies (and experts) interested in learning and talking about carbon and climate during SF Climate Week! 🎉

​​​From personal to professional carbon footprint, attendees walk away with tools and inspiration to take action on reducing our impact on the planet!

​Topics covered at SF Climate Week this year include Bay Area electric grid innovation, semiconductors (and AI), decarbonizing the maritime industry, sustainability in the wine industry, and more! [https://www.carbonnewbie.com/](https://www.carbonnewbie.com/)

​Co-Hosts:

[CNaught](https://www.cnaught.com/)

[Gigablue](https://www.gigablue.co/)

[Citizens for Responsible Energy Solutions](https://cresenergy.com/)

[Clever Carbon](https://clevercarbon.io/)

Venue Partner:

[Silicon Valley Bank](https://www.svb.com/)

​📺 LIVESTREAMING AVAILABLE

​ _We'll have a raffle with lots of fun goodies from Allbirds, Cotopaxi, Matthiasson Wineries Napa Tasting, and more! Come before 1:00pm to qualify for entry!_

​​ **AGENDA:**

12:15 pm: Doors Open (Raffle entries start)

1:00 pm: Programming Starts (Raffle entries end)

4:30 pm: Raffle Draw and Happy Hour

🔗 Full Program: https://www.carbonnewbie.com/#program

​​ _By registering for this event, you agree to share your registration information with our Hosts._

​About CNaught:

Trusted by buyers like Asana, Medium, and Tiger Global, CNaught makes it easy to drive real climate impact through high-quality carbon credit portfolios. We deliver access to sophisticated buying strategies, previously available only to the largest buyers, enabling companies of any size to take meaningful climate action. Learn more: [https://www.cnaught.com/](https://www.cnaught.com/)

​About Gigablue:

Gigablue offers a deep science-based marine carbon dioxide removal solution that helps companies achieve their net-zero goals by exporting CO2 to the deep ocean for long-term sequestration. Learn more: [https://www.gigablue.co](http://www.gigablue.co/)

​About Citizens for Responsible Energy Solutions:

Citizens for Responsible Energy Solutions (CRES) is a 501(c)(4) non-profit organization founded in 2013 to engage Republican policymakers and the public about responsible, conservative solutions to address our nation’s energy, economic, and environmental security while increasing America’s competitive edge. Learn more: [https://cresenergy.com/](https://cresenergy.com/)

About Clever Carbon:

At Clever Carbon, we teach people about carbon footprint in a hip and fun way! From content creation to carbon footprint workshops, we work with leading brands around the world to help raise carbon literacy because what gets measured gets changed! Learn more: [https://clevercarbon.io/](https://clevercarbon.io/)

About Event

​ **Event: Berkeley VC & Startup Summit**

​ **​Date:** Monday, April 7th, 2025

​ **Time:** 5:00 PM to 9:00 PM

​ **​Location:** Wells Fargo Room, Cheit Hall C420 at UC Berkeley

​ **​Co-hosted by:** BCAIA, Blackskies Investment, Ascend

​ **Supported by:** ⁠Berkeley M.E.T., CPGSA, AIEB, E@B, ⁠Free Ventures, Haas AI Club, ⁠World Leading Scientists Institute

​ **​Featured Speakers/Panelists:**

- ​Irving Hsu (Investor, Mayfield)

- ​Christopher Wan (Venture Partner, Bessemer Venture Partners)

- ​Carl Choi (Partner, Alumni Ventures)

- ​Misha Gordon-Rowe (Partner, Susa Ventures)

- ​Shyam Mani (Investor, AIX Ventures)

- ​Alvin Xiao (General Partner, Nyx Ventures)

- ​Shaheer (Principal, Susa Ventures; Berkeley Econ & Data Science, Class of ‘23)

- ​Saikat Chaudhuri (Professor, Haas and COE)

- ​Christopher Wong (Co-founder & CEO, stealth startup; JD/MBA from Northwestern University)

- ​Antoine Carriere (Co-founder, Brio; Angel Investor)

- ​Eddie Yu (Founder and CEO, OKOSIX)

- ​House Fund

- ​Shasi Pinninti (Partner, DRF; Berkeley M.E.T., Class of '26)


​ **Event Agenda:**

​ **5:00 - 5:30 PM** \| Check-in & Networking Mixer

​ **5:30 - 6:00 PM** \| Keynote Speaker

​ **6:00 - 7:00 PM** \| VC Insights Panel (panelists from Bessemer, Alumni Ventures, Susa, AIX, and Mayfield)

​ **7:00 - 8:00 PM** \| Ecosystem Spotlight (Christopher, Antoine, Eddy, House Fund, Shaheer (Susa Ventures), Saikat Chaudhuri)

​ **8:00  - 9:00 PM** \| Dinner Refreshments + Networking Session

​ **Event: Berkeley VC & Startup Summit**

​ **Supported by:** ⁠Berkeley M.E.T., CPGSA, AIEB, E@B, ⁠Free Ventures, Haas AI Club, ⁠World Leading Scientists Institute

​ **​Featured Speakers/Panelists:**

- ​Irving Hsu (Investor, Mayfield)

- ​Christopher Wan (Venture Partner, Bessemer Venture Partners)

- ​Carl Choi (Partner, Alumni Ventures)

- ​Misha Gordon-Rowe (Partner, Susa Ventures)

- ​Shyam Mani (Investor, AIX Ventures)

- ​Saikat Chaudhuri (Professor, Haas and COE)

- ​Christopher Wong (Co-founder & CEO, stealth startup; JD/MBA from Northwestern University)

- ​Antoine Carriere (Co-founder, Brio; Angel Investor)

- ​Eddie Yu (Founder and CEO, OKOSIX)

- ​House Fund

- ​Shasi Pinninti (Partner, DRF; Berkeley M.E.T., Class of '26)


​ **Event Agenda:**

​ **5:00 - 5:30 PM** \| Check-in & Networking Mixer

​ **5:30 - 6:00 PM** \| Keynote Speaker

​ **6:00 - 7:00 PM** \| VC Insights Panel (panelists from Bessemer, Alumni Ventures, Susa, AIX, and Mayfield)

​Founders Running Club (FRC) brings founders, investors, tech, creative people and startup enthusiasts together for weekly easy runs and networking. We like to be comfortable when we run and finish with coffee and conversations. Choose your pace or follow a pacer—pets, friends, family, are welcome.

Welcome! To join the event, please register below.

Request to Join

About Event

​Kick off SF Climate Week with a run in San Francisco's biggest and most beautiful park!

​Ammobia is hosting a run/walk for anyone in the climate tech / hard tech space, interested in starting the week outside, in one of the most beautiful urban parks in the country.

​We'll lead two groups Starting from near Lake Alvord in Golden Gate Park:

- ​A 3km walk around the Conservatory of Flowers \[ [Strava](https://www.strava.com/routes/3324206122505736272)\]

- ​A 7km park loop to a redwood grove, social pace, with different pace groups if needed. \[ [Strava](https://www.strava.com/routes/3324204734139442306)\]


​Both groups will end back near where we start for Coffee and pastries at \[Location TBD\] afterwards.

​If coming from downtown, the N-Judah can drop you off at Stanyan and Carl St, only a few blocks from our start point.

​Ammobia is on a mission to revolutionize the ammonia industry. We are a seed-stage startup developing Haber Bosch 2.0 – a next-generation ammonia synthesis process enabling cost-effective, clean ammonia production. Until now, ammonia production has been a highly polluting, steady-state, high inertia process. We are developing new regimes of physics and plant design that require dynamic processes, especially for ammonia production from intermittent renewable energy sources. Clean ammonia will support ammonia’s growing role in our decarbonized world, tackling some of the most difficult to abate sectors including chemicals, fertilizers, and heavy-duty transportation. We are supported by leading climate tech organizations including Starlight Ventures, Collaborative Fund, Third Derivative, Forbes 30u30, and more.

​Banc of Cal supports tech and life sciences startups with free bank accounts for pre-seed & seed companies, a perks platform, and a team of bankers to support founders as they scale. For VC-backed companies, we offer a non-dilutive venture debt product, lending from $1MM up to $60MM for growth, working capital or runway extension.

​ _By registering for this event, you agree to share your registration information with the organizers of SF Climate Week._

# Creating Change: The Power of Art in The Climate Movement + A Creative Workshop

Hosted by Karan Rathod, Andy Rapista & SF Climate Week

Apr

21

Monday, April 21

5:30 PM - 8:00 PM PDT

[San Francisco\\
\\
San Francisco, California](https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=San%20Francisco&query_place_id=ChIJIQBpAG2ahYAR_6128GcTUEo)

Welcome! To join the event, please register below.

Register

You will be asked to verify token ownership with your wallet.

About Event

​The sciences are no doubt critical in driving action and influencing climate policy, however, many people are inspired to take action once they have connected with the realities of climate change on an emotional level. This connection can be experienced through stories that move beyond mainstream representations, in the form of art – literature, music, visual art, theatre, film and more.

​This session aims to demonstrate and encourage art as an important mechanism to drive social change, focusing on climate conversations. Our panelists will highlight the role the arts have to play in driving social change, discuss their experiences of how art has had an impact on the climate conversation, and share their own creative projects.

​The session will also include an opportunity for you to workshop your own socially-driven creative ideas with the panelists, where you will leave with the foundations of a new (or existing) creative project.

The event will be co-hosted by [Andy Rapista](https://www.instagram.com/andyrapista/), climate activist and founder of [Mad Earth](https://madtravel.org/) and co-hosted and moderated by Karan Rathod, founder of [Alfaaz](http://www.alfaazcollective.com/) – a literature and arts collective that helps writers and artists get their creative work out, improve literary skills; and to leverage the arts for social change.

_By registering for this event, you agree to share your registration information with the organizers of SF Climate Week._

About Event

​ **About Event**

​​Kick off **San Francisco Climate Week** with **Mercury** and **Leap Forward Ventures** over drinks, light bites, and great conversation. Connect with fellow founders, investors, and industry leaders driving the next wave of climate innovation. Whether you're building, investing, or simply passionate about the future of climate tech, this is the perfect opportunity to network and exchange ideas.

​We look forward to seeing you there!

# ​ **​👋 Meet your hosts**

## ​​Mercury

​​Mercury lays the groundwork for ambitious companies to operate for excellence with banking and credit cards\* engineered for the startup journey. More than 200K companies choose Mercury to perform at their highest level. Mercury is dedicated to supporting climate tech founders and investors with dedicated perks for climate cos, opportunities to connect with investors via our Raise platform, and events and programming during SF and NY Climate Weeks.

​ _​\*Mercury is a financial technology company, not a bank. Banking services provided by Choice Financial Group, Column, N.A., and Evolve Bank & Trust, Members FDIC. The IO Card is issued by Patriot Bank, Member FDIC, pursuant to a license from Mastercard._

## ​​Leap Forward Ventures

​​Leap Forward Ventures is an early-stage climate tech firm focused on the energy transition, deep tech, and adaptation & resilience. They bring deep, high growth startup experience to help founders scale themselves and their companies to have maximum impact in decarbonizing our world.

# ​ **🤝 Who you’ll get to connect with**

​​Our team members can't wait to meet you. Read on to learn more about them, and be sure to say hello during the event.

​​Shelley Golan is a Senior Director of Relationship Management at Mercury with deep industry knowledge in Fintech, Deeptech & Climatetech. As a bi-coastal serial founder, startup ecosystem builder and advisor, she manages a portfolio of high-growth startups, offering guidance on venture debt and asset management, as well as connecting them to resources beyond banking.

​​David Rusenko was previously the founder & CEO of Weebly, which he grew to 350 people and a $365M acquisition by Square, where he went on to run global eCommerce. He is on the board of Building Decarb Coalition, an advisor to Climate Changemakers, and has over a decade of experience investing in and advising startups. He has spoken extensively on product-market fit and written about the climate tech landscape and idea space. He was born in France and grew up in Morocco.​

About Event

​Harvest is the smartest HVAC on Earth.

​Come take a live tour of a Harvester's home in the Mission to feel the magic of a Smart Thermal Battery. It's integrated heating, hot water, and air conditioning all in the same system. Not as sexy as an EV, but a lot comfier (and more impactful).

​It's heat pumps, but way smarter (and cheaper).

​More tours - including a happy hour - coming soon. Watch this space.

About Event

# ​ **🚀 The AI x Marketing Summit: Become AI-Native**

## ​ **Explore more details** **[here](https://aixmarketingsummit.com/)**

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=600/editor-images/y7/baf50602-8914-4888-8ce1-5b807593b6c3.png)

## ​ **The only Summit focused on transforming you into an AI-Native Marketer. Join us in San Francisco, CA**

​Every day, a new AI tool reshapes marketing. How do you cut through the noise to ignite growth _without_ losing strategic focus? This summit isn’t about chasing trends—it’s about mastering the mindset, tools, and processes to **become AI-Native**. Learn to prioritize growth strategy first, then apply AI for automation, scaling, and enhancing the human elements that build your brand. 💡

* * *

# ​ **⭐️ What’s On the Agenda?**

​ **A dynamic mix of vision, strategy, and hands-on skill-building:**

## ​ **✨ Vision & Strategy**

- ​ **Keynotes & Panels:** Hear from industry pioneers on AI’s role in marketing’s future.

- ​ **Networking & Growth Social:** Connect with innovators shaping the AI landscape.

- ​ **Workshops:** Dive into AI-driven content, email automation, and SEO.


## ​ **✨ Execution & Mastery**

- ​ **Breakout Sessions:** Tactical deep-dives on AI tools for growth hacking and brand-building.

- ​ **MasterClasses:** Transform how you work with cutting-edge platforms like Clay.

- ​ **Networking:** Forge partnerships to fuel your AI journey.


* * *

# ​ **🗣️ Meet the AI-Native Pioneers**

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=390/editor-images/p8/216c4613-1b5a-47c4-870b-ad2151ae654c.png)

## ​ [Tejas Manohar](https://www.linkedin.com/in/tejasmanohar/), Founder, Co-CEO, [HighTouch](https://hightouch.io/)

![User Uploaded Image](https://images.lumacdn.com/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=cover,dpr=2,quality=75,width=800,height=620.3125/editor-images/il/aa6a0c14-b232-4530-8f74-b986eccc9f36.webp)

## ​ [Jake Saper](https://www.linkedin.com/in/jakesaper/), General Partner, [Emergence Capital](https://www.emcap.com/)

## ​ **The only Summit focused on transforming you into an AI-Native Marketer. Join us in San Francisco, CA**

​Every day, a new AI tool reshapes marketing. How do you cut through the noise to ignite growth _without_ losing strategic focus? This summit isn’t about chasing trends—it’s about mastering the mindset, tools, and processes to **become AI-Native**. Learn to prioritize growth strategy first, then apply AI for automation, scaling, and enhancing the human elements that build your brand. 💡

- ​ **Workshops:** Dive into AI-driven content, email automation, and SEO.


## ​ **✨ Execution & Mastery**

- ​ **Breakout Sessions:** Tactical deep-dives on AI tools for growth hacking and brand-building.

- ​ **MasterClasses:** Transform how you work with cutting-edge platforms like Clay.

- ​ **Networking:** Forge partnerships to fuel your AI journey.

## ​ **The only Summit focused on transforming you into an AI-Native Marketer. Join us in San Francisco, CA**

​Every day, a new AI tool reshapes marketing. How do you cut through the noise to ignite growth _without_ losing strategic focus? Learn to prioritize growth strategy first, then apply AI for automation, scaling, and enhancing the human elements that build your brand. 💡

- ​ **Networking & Growth Social:** Connect with innovators shaping the AI landscape.

- ​ **Workshops:** Dive into AI-driven content, email automation, and SEO.


## ​ **✨ Execution & Mastery**

- ​ **Breakout Sessions:** Tactical deep-dives on AI tools for growth hacking and brand-building.

- ​ **MasterClasses:** Transform how you work with cutting-edge platforms like Clay.

- ​ **Networking:** Forge partnerships to fuel your AI journey.

# ​ **🔨 Hands-On Workshops**

## ​ **Learn by doing:**

- ​ **Clay MasterClass: Transform your workflow with Yash Tekriwal (Clay’s Head of Education).**

- ​ **AI x GTM: Automate GTM at scale with Sybill.ai**

- ​ **AI x Content: Repurpose content across channels with Chang Chen (Reforge,** **[Otter.ai](http://otter.ai/)** **).**

- ​ **AI x SEO: Create AI-powered content that ranks** **_and_** **resonates.**


## ​ **Takeaways you’ll use immediately:**

​ **✅ Automate audience targeting and personalized messaging.**

**✅ Turn webinars into blogs, ads, nurture sequences, and more.**

**✅ Master tools like Clay,** **[Writer.com](http://writer.com/)** **, and AI agents for growth.**

* * *

# ​ **🤨 Why Attend?**

## ​ **This is the only summit where you’ll:**

1. ​ **Shift from AI-Curious to AI-Native: Adopt a strategic framework to integrate AI without losing your brand’s humanity.**

2. ​ **Learn from Practitioners, Not Theorists: CMOs, growth leaders, and AI founders share** **_exact_** **workflows and tools.**

3. ​ **Network with the AI Vanguard: Forge connections with 500+ marketers, VCs, and tool-builders shaping the future.**

- ​ **AI x SEO: Create AI-powered content that ranks** **_and_** **resonates.**


## ​ **Takeaways you’ll use immediately:**

​ **✅ Automate audience targeting and personalized messaging.**

**✅ Master tools like Clay,** **[Writer.com](http://writer.com/)** **, and AI agents for growth.**

1. ​ **Shift from AI-Curious to AI-Native: Adopt a strategic framework to integrate AI without losing your brand’s humanity.**

3. ​ **Network with the AI Vanguard: Forge connections with 500+ marketers, VCs, and tool-builders shaping the future.**

Request to Join

About Event

​Most Climate Week events talk about change. This event gives us all a chance to build it. Join us to close out SF Climate Week with creativity, community, and hope.

​

We’ll kick off with a series of fast-paced lightning talks from experts, implementers and funders in the climate space, including from Project Drawdown, Vibrant Data Labs and Kiva — highlighting data and real-world insights on how women-led climate initiatives are consistently underfunded. These quick, compelling shares will set the stage for collective action.

​

From there, the room becomes a workshop. You’ll join a small table group together with the panellists and designers from IDEO [.](https://ideo.org/) orgto use the tools of design futuring to create an object of the future: a tangible artifact that represents the regenerative, gender-just world we’re working toward.

Expect conversation, collaboration, and a creative close to SF Climate Week where you’ll have the opportunity to synthesize everything you’ve learned and questioned during the week. Refreshments and light appetizers by women-owned businesses will be served!

​ _By registering for this event, you agree to share your registration information with the organizers of SF Climate Week_

# Drop-In A Cappella Workshop

[Bay Area A Cappella](https://lu.ma/acahub?k=c)

Apr

9

Wednesday, April 9

6:30 PM - 9:30 PM PDT

Register to See Address

San Francisco, California

Welcome! To join the event, please get your ticket below.

Get Ticket

You will be asked to verify token ownership with your wallet.

About Event

​​An experiment, a spin on our usual format, focused on connection and growth.

​Everyone will come with the music learned (able to sing through with few / no mistakes). We'll be off music for the second half, focusing on connecting with the music and each other, and working in smaller ensembles to hone our skills.

​We'll be singing I Just Called To Say I Love You, as covered by Pentatonix.

​PREPARATION REQUIRED,

​PREVIOUS EXPERIENCE RECOMMENDED (intermediate and advanced singers - we'll be singing 2 or 1 person per part). Test if you're ready by playing the original on a speaker and singing along on your part, and then listen back.

​$5 minimum, but no one turned away for lack of funds (email robert.acahub@gmail.com).

​

Sheet music PDF provided - please bring a device to view it, or print your own copy.

​FYI, there will be photos and videos taken at the event which may be used in future marketing materials.

# AI After Hours @ GitHub w/ Encord

[Artificially Intelligent](https://lu.ma/artificially-intelligent?k=c)

Apr

10

Thursday, April 10

5:30 PM - 8:30 PM PDT

Register to See Address

San Francisco, California

Welcome! To join the event, please register below.

Register

You will be asked to verify token ownership with your wallet.

About Event

​ **Join Encord for an exciting evening of AI/ML talks at GitHub HQ!** ​

​Connect with fellow AI/ML practitioners, learn from industry experts & enjoy a slice of pizza 🍕

​Can't make it in person? No problem! Register to receive the livestream link & join us virtually.

* * *

## ​Agenda

​5:30pm: Doors open

6pm - 8:00pm: Lightning talks ⚡

8:00pm - 8:30pm: Networking

## ​​​Talks

​ **"Building the Perception Stack for the Home"**

Vasu Raman, Co-Founder & Head of Engineering at Sauron

​ **“Learnings from Scaling An AI Company & Our Vision for the Future”**

Ulrik Stig Hansen, Co-Founder & President of Encord

​ **"General Intelligence is Multimodal"**

Keegan McCallum, Head of ML Infrastructure at Luma AI

​

_Check out our_ _[YouTube channel](https://www.youtube.com/@encord)_ _to catch up on talks from our previous speakers._

* * *

## ​About Encord

​ [Encord](https://encord.com/) is a multimodal data platform for AI. We empower AI teams to manage, curate, and label massive datasets - including images, videos, audio, text, and more - on one unified platform. With AI-assisted and human-in-the-loop workflows, we help you build better models faster.

​ 🤔 Want to learn more?

🤳 Follow Encord on [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/company/encord-team/)

​​ 📈 We’re hiring, [join our team](https://encord.com/careers/)
